### ========================================
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tickets?category=Documentation

### ========================================
### GET - Paged tickets (default: page 0, size 5, sortBy createdAt, desc)
### ========================================
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tickets/paged?page=0&size=5

### ========================================
### GET - Paged tickets with custom sort (sortBy createdAt, direction desc)
### ========================================
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tickets/paged?page=0&size=5&sortBy=createdAt&direction=desc

### ========================================
### GET - Paged tickets - second page
### ========================================
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tickets/paged?page=1&size=5&sortBy=createdAt&direction=desc

### ========================================
### GET - Paged tickets sorted by priority ascending
### ========================================
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tickets/paged?page=0&size=3&sortBy=priority&direction=asc

### ========================================
### GET - One ticket by ID (replace with real ID from GET /api/tickets above)
### ========================================
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tickets/REPLACE_WITH_REAL_ID

### ========================================
### GET - Missing ticket (should return 404)
### ========================================
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tickets/000000000000000000000000

### ========================================
### POST - Create a valid ticket
### ========================================
POST http://localhost:8080/api/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Cannot connect to VPN",
  "description": "VPN connection fails with timeout error",
  "category": "Network",
  "priority": "High",
  "createdBy": "alice@example.com"
}

### ========================================
### POST - Create an invalid ticket (empty fields - should return 400)
### ========================================
POST http://localhost:8080/api/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "",
  "description": "",
  "category": "",
  "priority": "",
  "createdBy": ""
}
